steps.content:
Count the total number of data points, $n$. Here, there are 10 values.

Since $n=10$ is an even number, the median is found by taking the average of the two middle values. These correspond to the $5^{\text{th}}$ and $6^{\text{th}}$ positions:

$$
\begin{aligned}
\frac{n}{2} &= \frac{10}{2} = 5^{\text{th}} \text{ value} \\
\frac{n}{2} + 1 &= 6^{\text{th}} \text{ value}
\end{aligned}
$$

